The paper discusses a security architecture for cyber-physical systems, which involves the integration of multiple systems and their functional interdependencies. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on the operability of the cyber-physical system, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. The paper also discusses the recovery of the affected system functionality, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. The paper also discusses the impact of the cyber-attack on the electric load distribution in the power grid, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the simulation results, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category.
